Amid a volcanic performance full of untruths and bulldozer-style tactics, President Trump notably refused to condemn white supremacy when asked.Both he and Joe Biden lobbed personal attacks and expressed a level of acrid contempt for each other unheard-of in modern American politics.
Here are six takeaways from the debate.
The chaos of the debate has left allies and rivals alike questioning American democracy and the country’s place in the world.
In a polarized America, commentators online could finally agree on something.
President Trump’s first debate with Joe Biden was marked by interruptions, accusations and, at times, flat-out falsehoods.
Joe Biden faced a barrage of attacks, but he fired back several times in ways that drifted outside expectations.
